# MyExpenses

requires 'Python 2.7, PyQt4, numpy, matplotlib, MySQL, drivers for the PyQt4-MySQL interface (for Ubuntu: apt-get install libqt4-sql-mysql)'
run 'python main.py'

before running the programm you need to:
	create a database named 'myexpenses': create database if not exists myexpenses;
	(optional - create a new database user: create user '<username>'@'<hostname>' identified by '<password>'; grant usage on *.* to '<username>'@'<hostname>' identified by '<password>';  # hostname=localhost for your local MySQL version)
	grant privileges to a user on that database: grant all privileges on myexpenses.* to '<username>'@'<hostname>'; flush privileges;  # hostname=localhost for your local MySQL version

Do not use the application as the mysql root!
